messages.content:
This being at rare when most of the other ??? cards are at lower rarities is a huge clue. Most snecko decks will end up with lots of muddle tools, and nearly any card that has it's cost reduced by 2 or more energy regularly is going to be fantastic. On top of that, several powerful engine and scaling cards cost 3 energy (forms being the big ones), which gives you the chance to roll those in key fights, or if you get lucky with timing, the ability to lock in one at a campfire. I think this is easily one of sneckos' best unidentified cards and it is always tempting at shops or as a boss reward if you have even a little bit of muddle, master eye or snecko eye. Even some of the worst possible rolls will normally still be okay since you can reduce the cost so reliably on snecko.

Upgrade is not great, assuming that you want this to become a form/corruption (most just remove ethereal, corruption+ costs 2 energy and will be removed from the pool). You also would probably rather spend a campfire action locking this into something powerful or that can give your deck direction rather than upgrading it. Gets a little better with necronomicon to let you double up on 3 cost attacks, and becomes far better when you have selected characters with particularly powerful 3 cost cards (defect, ironclad, silent, etc.). Unidentified Egg makes this card much better (as it does for every unidentified card).
i always pick these. and identifying it can cause your deck to go completely bonkers, or save your ass (Wraith Form)
I think this cards upgrade is fine. Its a decent click when you don't have anything better, since you ideally want to ID the card later you can think about as upgrading the card ahead of time

A lot of this cards good cards are not form cards, at least for pure snecko they aren't; so the upgrade can go into something valuable. Its at least better then most other ? card upgrades which might not even be IDed
the only misses here could be <shooting star>, <finger of death> or <gladiator form>
